description:
Now, we explore the Albigensians. Much like the Waldensians who remained true to God's word, the Albigensians had a similar faith based in Southern France. During the reign of Pope Innocent III, at the start of the 13th century, numerous groups were persecuted, and in particular the Albigensians. Over a 20-year period, the Pope attempted to wipe out the faithful, Bible believing worshippers in Southern France. 

To find out more information about the Albigensians check out our extended article.
http://www.lineagejourney.com/uncategorized/the-albigenses/
